      "u_instruction": "Provide a formal, objective response that cites general research consensus without using lists, focusing on a single recommended frequency range.",
      "s_gold": "Hello! I'm happy to help you with your question.\n\nTo reap the benefits of game night, it's recommended that families conduct it regularly, but the frequency can vary depending on your family's schedule and preferences. Here are a few suggestions:\n\n1. Weekly: Hosting game night every week can help create a consistent bonding experience for your family. It can be a fun way to unwind and spend quality time together after a long week.\n2. Bi-weekly: If weekly game nights aren't feasible, consider hosting them every other week. This frequency still allows for regular bonding time while giving you and your family members some breathing room.\n3. Monthly: If you're struggling to fit game night into your schedule, aim for at least once a month. This can still provide opportunities for team-building and create lasting memories.\n\nRemember, the most crucial aspect is to choose a frequency that works best for your family and stick to it. Consistency is key to reaping the benefits of game night.\n\nIn addition, you can mix things up by playing different games, incorporating new members, or even hosting virtual game nights if needed. The essential part is to prioritize quality time with your loved ones and make it an enjoyable experience for everyone.\n\nI hope this helps! If you have any more questions or concerns, please feel free to ask.",
