within my training distribution, not a verified mathematical certainty.\n\n**Example Application**:\nIf you ask, \"What is the current stock price of Apple?\"\n*   **Direct Answer**: $175.43 (if real-time data is available).\n*   **Confidence**: 95% (based on the timestamp of the retrieved data).\n*   **Explanation**: I retrieved this from the live market feed. However, stock prices fluctuate every second, so this is a snapshot. If no live feed is available, I would state the last known price from my training data with lower confidence and a disclaimer about the date.\n",
