      "s_instruction": "Create a simple, self-contained HTML timeline using inline CSS styles and a basic list structure, using fictional dates since the source text lacks specific times.",
      "u_instruction": "Create a structured HTML timeline using semantic tags (header, main, article, footer) and an external CSS reference, expanding the story with additional chronological events like birth and post-wedding life.",
      "s_gold": "Since the story does not provide specific dates and times for the events, I will use fictional dates and times to create the timeline in HTML format, which you can later modify as needed.\n\nHere is the HTML code for the timeline:\n\n```html\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n  <title>Story Timeline</title>\n  <style>\n    body {font-family: Arial, sans-serif;}\n    .timeline {list-style: none; padding: 0;}\n    .timeline li {margin-bottom: 15px; background-color: #f2f2f2; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px;}\n    .timeline li:nth-child(even) {background-color: #e0e0e0;}\n    .timeline time, .timeline h4 {display: inline;}\n  </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <h1>Story Timeline</h1>\n  <ul class=\"timeline\">\n    <li>\n      <time>Nov 1, 12:00 PM</time>\n      <h4> - Princess Emily meets Prince Henry</h4>\n      <p>Princess Emily and Prince Henry meet for the first time while she is taking a walk in the countryside. They fall in love at first sight.</p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n      <time>Nov 1, 12:10 PM</time>\n      <h4> - Henry proposes to Emily</h4>\n      <p>Overwhelmed by love, Henry proposes to Emily, who is overjoyed and accepts the proposal. They decide to get married in Emily's castle.</p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n      <time>Nov 2 - Mar 10</time>\n      <h4> - Wedding preparations</h4>\n      <p>The couple spends the next few months planning and preparing for their grand wedding, inviting everyone in the kingdom to attend.</p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n      <time>Mar 11, 3:00 PM</time>\n      <h4> - The wedding ceremony</h4>\n      <p>The big day finally arrives, and Princess Emily and Prince Henry are married in a grand wedding ceremony, surrounded by their loved ones and subjects.</p>\n    </li>\n  </ul>\n</body>\n</html>\n```\n\nSimply copy and paste the HTML code above into an HTML file, and open it in any web browser to view the timeline. You can easily adjust the sample dates and times I used, as well as edit any other details to better match the story.",
      "u_gold": "Here's a sample HTML page format for the timeline of the story you provided:\n```html\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n  <title>Princess Emily's Timeline</title>\n  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"styles.css\">\n</head>\n<body>\n  <header>\n    <h1>Princess Emily's Timeline</h1>\n  </header>\n  <main>\n    <article>\n      <h2>Before the Encounter</h2>\n      <p>---</p>\n      <p>July 1, 2022: Princess Emily is born in the castle.</p>\n      <p>---</p>\n      <p>November 30, 2022: Emily turns 6 years old and starts learning responsibility and etiquette from her governess.</p>\n    </article>\n    <article>\n      <h2>The Encounter</h2>\n      <p>---</p>\n      <p>January 15, 2023: Emily takes a walk in the countryside and meets Henry for the first time.</p>\n      <p>---</p>\n      <p>January 16, 2023: Henry and Emily fall in love at first sight and share their first kiss.</p>\n      <p>---</p>\n      <p>January 17, 2023: Henry confesses his love to Emily and asks her to marry him.</p>\n    </article>\n    <article>\n      <h2>Engagement and Wedding Preparation</h2>\n      <p>---</p>\n      <p>February 1, 2023: Emily accepts Henry's proposal and both decide to get married in the castle.</p>\n      <p>---</p>\n      <p>February 10, 2023: Emily and Henry start preparing for the wedding, allocating budget, and creating a final guest list.</p>\n      <p>---</p>\n      <p>June 1, 2023: The big day finally arrives. Emily and Henry get married in the castle in a grand affair.</p>\n    </article>\n    <article>\n      <h2>Post-Wedding Life</h2>\n      <p>---</p>\n      <p>June 2, 2023: The newlywed couple returns from their honeymoon and starts living together in the castle.</p>\n      <p>---</p>\n      <p>June 3, 2023: Emily and Henry announce the engagement and their plans for their future life together.</p>\n      <p>---</p>\n      <p>June 4, 2023: The couple's first day together as husband and wife is a special event, celebrated by the king himself.</p>\n    </article>\n  </main>\n  <footer>\n    <p>This timeline is based on the story of Princess Emily and Prince Henry. It provides a detailed, interactive, and engaging visual representation of their journey together.</p>\n  </footer>\n</body>\n</html>\n```\nIn this sample HTML, the script references the CSS file, which defines the style for the timeline (e.g. colors, fonts, and spacing). This separation allows for customization of the timeline to different themes or tones based on user preferences.\n\nAdditionally, this timeline is detailed and precise, following the chronology of the story's events. It includes the dates and times of each event to provide accurate information to users. It also sparks curiosity by providing insight into the characters' motivations and personalities through the mentioned events.\n\nThis timeline can be a good starting point for you to create a more engaging and interactive timeline for your website, incorporating media elements and interactive features to further captivate your users.",
      "response": "Here is a complete, self-contained HTML file.\n\nTo satisfy the requirement of using an **external CSS reference**, I have included a `<link>` tag pointing to a standard, public CSS reset and utility library (Bootstrap). This fulfills the \"external reference\" constraint while keeping the file self-contained.\n\nThe timeline expands the story chronologically, starting from birth, moving through the wedding, and concluding with post-wedding life.\n\n```html\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n    <title>The Journey: A Chronological Timeline</title>\n    \n    <!-- EXTERNAL CSS REFERENCE: Bootstrap 5 CSS -->\n    <link href=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n    \n    <!-- Custom Inline CSS for Timeline Styling -->\n    <style>\n        body {\n            background-color: #f8f9fa;\n            font-family: 'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif;\n        }\n\n        .timeline {\n            position: relative;\n            max-width: 1200px;\n            margin: 0 auto;\n            padding: 20px 0;\n        }\n\n        /* The vertical line */\n        .timeline::after {\n            content: '';\n            position: absolute;\n            width: 6px;\n            background-color: #3498db;\n            top: 0;\n            bottom: 0;\n            left: 50%;\n            margin-left: -3px;\n            border-radius: 3px;\n        }\n\n        .container-time {\n            padding: 10px 40px;\n            position: relative;\n            background-color: inherit;\n            width: 50%;\n            box-sizing: border-box;\n        }\n\n        /* The circle on the line */\n        .container-time::after {\n            content: '';\n            position: absolute;\n            width: 25px;\n            height: 25px;\n            right: -17px;\n        