      "s_gold": "Since the story does not provide specific dates and times for the events, I will use fictional dates and times to create the timeline in HTML format, which you can later modify as needed.\n\nHere is the HTML code for the timeline:\n\n```html\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n  <title>Story Timeline</title>\n  <style>\n    body {font-family: Arial, sans-serif;}\n    .timeline {list-style: none; padding: 0;}\n    .timeline li {margin-bottom: 15px; background-color: #f2f2f2; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px;}\n    .timeline li:nth-child(even) {background-color: #e0e0e0;}\n    .timeline time, .timeline h4 {display: inline;}\n  </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <h1>Story Timeline</h1>\n  <ul class=\"timeline\">\n    <li>\n      <time>Nov 1, 12:00 PM</time>\n      <h4> - Princess Emily meets Prince Henry</h4>\n      <p>Princess Emily and Prince Henry meet for the first time while she is taking a walk in the countryside. They fall in love at first sight.</p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n      <time>Nov 1, 12:10 PM</time>\n      <h4> - Henry proposes to Emily</h4>\n      <p>Overwhelmed by love, Henry proposes to Emily, who is overjoyed and accepts the proposal. They decide to get married in Emily's castle.</p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n      <time>Nov 2 - Mar 10</time>\n      <h4> - Wedding preparations</h4>\n      <p>The couple spends the next few months planning and preparing for their grand wedding, inviting everyone in the kingdom to attend.</p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n      <time>Mar 11, 3:00 PM</time>\n      <h4> - The wedding ceremony</h4>\n      <p>The big day finally arrives, and Princess Emily and Prince Henry are married in a grand wedding ceremony, surrounded by their loved ones and subjects.</p>\n    </li>\n  </ul>\n</body>\n</html>\n```\n\nSimply copy and paste the HTML code above into an HTML file, and open it in any web browser to view the timeline. You can easily adjust the sample dates and times I used, as well as ed