      "s_gold": "Absolutely! Here's a 2-minute speech you can use to welcome your guests to your dim sum themed 36th birthday party:\n\n\"Good evening, everyone! Welcome to my 36th birthday party, where we're celebrating the joy of dim sum! For those who may be new to this delicious Chinese cuisine, dim sum is a style of Cantonese dining that involves small, bite-sized portions of food served in steamer baskets or on small plates.\n\nTonight, we'll be indulging in a variety of dim sum dishes, from classic har gow and siu mai to more adventurous options like chive dumplings and rice rolls with sweet and savory fillings. And of course, no dim sum feast would be complete without a selection of teas to pair with our meal.\n\nBut this party is about more than just food \u2013 it's also a celebration of community and connection. As we gather around the table, let's take a moment to appreciate the people in our lives who bring us joy and fulfillment. Whether you're a longtime friend, a beloved family member, or a new connection made today, I'm grateful for your presence here.\n\nSo let's dig in, enjoy the feast, and savor the company of those around us. May this birthday party be a time of celebration, connection, and joy for all of us! Cheers!\"\n\nRemember to always prioritize safety when hosting a party, especially when it comes to food preparation and handling. Make sure to follow proper food safety guidelines and allergies/dietary restrictions of your guests.",
      "u_gold": "Sure, here's a possible speech you could use to welcome people to your dim sum themed 36th birthday party:\n\n\"Hello, everyone! Welcome to my dim sum themed 36th birthday party! I'm so glad you could join me to celebrate this special day.\n\nFirst of all, I want to thank each and every one of you for being here. Your presence means the world to me, and I'm honored to have such wonderful friends and family in my life.\n\nNow, let's talk about the theme of the party. Dim sum, for those who may not know, is a style of Cantonese cuisine that involves serving small, bite-sized portions of food in steamer baskets or on small plates. It's a tradition that's deeply rooted in Chinese culture, and it's a favorite of mine.\n\nI chose this theme for my birthday party because I wanted to share a little bit of my heritage with all of you. Growing up, my family would often go out for dim sum on special occasions, and it's a tradition that I've continued to enjoy as an adult.\n\nBut enough about me! Let's talk about the food. We have an amazing spread of dim sum dishes for you to enjoy, all made with love and care by our talented chefs. From har gow and siu mai to egg tarts and turnip cakes, there's something for everyone to enjoy.\n\nI hope you'll take the time to try a little bit of everything, and don't be afraid to ask for seconds (or thirds, or fourths...you get the idea). And of course, no dim sum meal is complete without a pot of tea, so be sure to pour yourself a cup and enjoy the warm, soothing flavors.\n\nIn addition to the food, we have some fun activities planned for the evening. We'll have a photo booth set up with props and costumes, so be sure to take some silly photos to commemorate the occasion. And later on, we'll have a game of dim sum trivia, so be sure to study up on your dim sum facts and trivia.\n\nBefore we get started, I want to say a special thank you to [name of person who helped with the party planning and organization]. Without their help, this party wouldn't have been possible, and I'm so grateful for their support.\n\nAnd finally, I want to thank all of you again for being here. Your presence means the world to me, and I hope you have a wonderful time enjoying the food, drinks, and company. Thank you, and let's get this party started!\"\n\nI hope this speech helps to welcome your guests to your dim sum themed birthday party and sets the tone for a fun and memorable evening!",
      "response": "Good evening, everyone!\n\nWelcome to a night of celebration, laughter, and the most important ingredient of all: community. I am so incredibly honored to have you here for my 36th birthday.\n\nThirty-six years ago, I was born into a world that felt vast and sometimes overwhelming. But looking back, I realize that my true foundation wasn't built on grand milestones, but on the small, warm moments shared with the people who love me. That's why today, we are celebrating with a theme that speaks directly to my roots: Dim Sum.\n\nFor many of you, dim sum isn't just food; it's a memory. It's the smell of steaming siu mai drifting through the kitchen, the sticky sweetness of red bean soup, and the communal joy of sharing a plate. It represents a heritage of togetherness, where the act of eating is an act of connection. As we sit here tonight, surrounded by these delicious treats, let's honor the generations that taught us that life is best savored in small, shared bites.\n\nTo make this evening even more special, we've set up a fun photo booth right here in the corner. Whether you're dressed up in your finest or just wearing your \"best dim sum outfit,\" I encourage you to grab a prop, strike a pose, and capture these memories. Let's create a gallery of our best moments together.\n\nBefore we dive into the feast, I must make one very important request. Please, take a moment to review the food safety protocols posted at the entrance. We are committed to keeping this party safe and healthy for everyone. Please wash your hands thoroughly before serving yourself, use the provided utensils, and keep an eye on your food to ensure it stays fresh. Your health is the most important part of this celebration, and I appreciate your cooperation in maintaining our safe environment.\n\nFinally, a huge thank you to the incredible team that made this possible. To my parents, whose love is the recipe for everything I am; to my siblings, who are the best chefs in the family; and to my friends, who have been my constant companions. Special thanks to [Name], who organized the decorations, [Name], who helped with the music, and [Name], who ensured the food safety protocols were followed with such care. You are the backbone of this party.\n\nSo, let's raise our glasses. To 36 years of growth, to the delicious dim sum ahead, and to the beautiful community that makes every birthday worth celebrating. Cheers!\n",
