      "response": "I cannot provide a specific embed code because **you have not included the text, link, or source material** in your message that contains the embed instructions or the code itself. Without the specific content you are referring to, I cannot generate the unique code required for that particular resource.\n\nHowever, I can provide a **detailed, step-by-step guide** on how to locate, select, copy, and paste an embed code into a standard website editor (such as WordPress, Wix, Squarespace, or custom HTML editors) once you have found the source.\n\n### Step-by-Step Guide to Embedding Content\n\n#### Step 1: Locate the Embed Code\n1.  **Find the Source**: Go to the website, video platform (e.g., YouTube, Vimeo), or document where the content you want to embed is hosted.\n2.  **Access Share Options**: Look for a button labeled **\"Share,\" \"Embed,\"** or an icon resembling a link chain or a document with a plus sign.\n3.  **Select \"Embed\"**: Choose the option to embed the content.\n    *   *Note*: Some platforms (like YouTube) will automatically generate a code block for you. Others may require you to manually copy a snippet of HTML code provided in the \"Embed HTML\" section.\n4.  **Copy the Code**: Highlight the entire block of code (usually starting with `<iframe...` or `<script...`) and copy it to your clipboard.\n\n#### Step 2: Prepare Your Website Editor\n1.  **Log In**: Access the dashboard of the website builder or CMS where you want to publish the content.\n2.  **Navigate to the Page**: Open the specific page where the embed should appear.\n3.  **Enter Edit Mode**: Ensure you are in \"Edit Mode\" or \"Visual Editor.\"\n\n#### Step 3: Insert the Embed Code\nThere are two common methods depending on your editor:\n\n**Method A: Using the \"Embed\" or \"Insert\" Block (Recommended for most modern editors)**\n1.  Click the **\"+\"** button or the **\"Insert Block\"** menu in your editor toolbar.\n2.  Search for and select **\"Embed Code,\" \"HTML,\"** or **\"Embed.\"**\n3.  A text area will appear. Paste the code you copied in Step 1 into this box.\n4.  Click **\"Insert,\" \"Add,\"** or **\"Update.\"**\n\n**Method B: Using the \"Custom HTML\" Feature**\n1.  Click the **\"+\"** button or **\"Insert Block\"** menu.\n2.  Select **\"Custom HTML\"** (sometimes labeled as \"Code\" or \"Text\").\n3.  Paste the code into the text area.\n4.  Click **\"Insert.\"**\n\n#### Step 4: Verify and Publish\n1.  **Preview**: Click the **\"Preview\"** or **\"View Page\"** button to ensure the code rendered correctly and the content appears as expected.\n2.  **Adjustments**: If the content is misaligned or missing, check for syntax errors in the code or ensure the source URL is correct.\n3.  **Publish**: Once verified, click **\"Publish\"** or **\"Update Page\"** to make the changes live.\n\nIf you can provide the specific text or link you are working with, I would be happy to help you extract the correct code or troubleshoot any specific issues you are facing with your website editor.\n",
