      "u_gold": "To create a DAG (Directed Acyclic Graph) file for Apache Airflow to execute an SQL query on a MySQL database and transfer it to another MySQL database, follow the steps below:\n\n1. Install Apache Airflow:\n\nFirst, install Apache Airflow using the instructions in the [official documentation](https://airflow.apache.org/docs/apache-airflow/stable/start/miniconda.html).\n2. Create a DAG:\n\nCreate a new directory (e.g., `mysql_to_mysql_dag`) to store your DAG files. Inside the directory, create a `__init__.py` file to make it a Python package.\n3. Create the DAG file:\n\nIn the `mysql_to_mysql_dag` directory, create a file named `mysql_to_mysql.py`. This file should contain the definition of your DAG. Here's an example:\n```python\nimport os\nfrom sqlalchemy import create_engine\nfrom airflow import DAG\nfrom airflow.providers.mysql.operators.mysql import MySqlOperator\nfrom airflow.providers.mysql.transfer import MySQLToMySQLTransfer\n\ndefault_args = {\n    'owner': 'airflow',\n    'depends_on_past': False,\n    'email_on_failure': False,\n    'email_on_retry': False,\n    'retries': 1,\n    'retry_delay': timedelta(minutes=5),\n}\n\ndef get_conn_string(database_type: str, target_host: str):\n    if database_type == 'source':\n        conn_str = f\"mysql://{database_user}:{database_password}@{source_host}/{source_database}\"\n    else:\n        conn_str = f\"mysql://{database_user}:{database_password}@{target_host}/{target_database}\"\n    return conn_str\n\ndefmysql_to_mysql():\n    dag = DAG(\n        'mysql_to_mysql',\n        default_args=default_args,\n        description='Transfer data from one MySQL database to another',\n        schedule_interval=timedelta(days=1),\n    )\n\n    source_database = 'your_source_database'\n    target_database = 'your_target_database'\n    source_host = 'your_source_mysql_host'\n    target_host = 'your_target_mysql_host'\n    database_user = 'your_mysql_user'\n    database_password = 'your_mysql_password'\n    t