      "s_instruction": "Summarize the meeting minutes by focusing on the technical migration of the existing 'Pi' affiliate system to a new platform and the general modernization of the user experience.",
      "u_instruction": "Summarize the meeting minutes by explicitly including the specific request for a new quote and the plan to update the backwards-end operations (BOS).",
      "s_gold": "Based on the meeting minutes, Pulmuone is looking to reorganize their website, specifically the Pulman Lohas site, to improve the user experience and update the membership system. The current system requires customers to sign up for membership to purchase products, and Pulmuone is looking to migrate the membership system to a new platform.\n\nCurrently, the site uses an internal affiliate business system called \"Pi\" to manage memberships, but this system will be replaced with a new, easier-to-use platform. The new system will allow customers to login and access membership-related features, such as viewing and managing their membership status and purchases.\n\nAdditionally, Pulmuone is looking to update the manager page on the site to make it easier to operate and maintain. This will include the ability to update and manage membership information, as well as the ability to push changes to the live site.\n\nOverall, Pulmuone is looking to modernize and improve the user experience of their website, while also making it easier to manage and maintain the membership system.",
      "u_gold": "During the meeting, it was discussed that Pulmuone is planning to reorganize the Pulman Lohas website to better incorporate an offline affiliate business and membership system for customers. Currently, customers who purchase products offline are offered membership and can use employee goods and earn points on the site. The goal is to change the login and membership-related functions to better support the new membership system.\n\nThe team also mentioned the \"Pi\" system, which is used internally for the affiliate business. They want to revise the manager page to better accommodate the updated membership and login features. Finally, they requested a quote for creating a new site and updating the backwards-end operations (BOS) to support these changes.",
      "response": "The meeting minutes highlight a strategic shift to modernize the existing 'Pi' affiliate system. The primary technical objective is the migration of the current infrastructure to a new platform, which will simultaneously drive a comprehensive overhaul of the user experience to meet contemporary standards.\n\nKey action items identified include:\n*   **Request for Quote:** A formal request for a new quote was explicitly approved to facilitate the costs associated with this migration and modernization efforts.\n*   **Back-End Operations (BOS) Update:** The team confirmed the plan to update the Back-End Operations (BOS) to ensure seamless integration with the new platform and to support the enhanced user interface.\n",
