      "u_instruction": "Explain which appliance can be used to cook rice between a refrigerator and a water dispenser.",
      "s_gold": "Neither a refrigerator nor a water dispenser can be used to cook rice. A refrigerator is a home appliance that maintains a low temperature, typically between 37 and 45 degrees Fahrenheit, for the storage of food. A water dispenser is a device that dispenses water from a reservoir. Both of these appliances lack the necessary components to cook rice, such as a heating element and a pot.\r\n\r\nA rice cooker is an appliance that is specifically designed for cooking rice. It typically has a heating element, a pot, and a timer. The user adds rice and water to the pot, sets the timer, and the rice cooker does the rest. The rice cooker will heat the water until it reaches a boiling point, then it will switch to a low heat setting to simmer the rice until it is cooked through.\r\n\r\nIf you do not have a rice cooker, you can cook rice on the stovetop. To do this, you will need a pot, a stovetop, and a measuring cup. Add rice and water to the pot according to the ratio on the package of rice. Bring the water to a boil, then reduce the heat to low and simmer for 20-25 minutes, or until the rice is cooked through.",
