      "response": "# Comprehensive Scoring Policy Document\n\n## 1. Introduction and Scope\nThis document establishes the standardized framework for evaluating performance across all designated assessment categories. The policy ensures fairness, transparency, and consistency in scoring by defining clear criteria, difficulty tiers, and a hierarchical ranking system. All evaluators must adhere strictly to these guidelines to maintain the integrity of the results.\n\n## 2. Core Scoring Rules\nThe fundamental mechanics of the scoring system are governed by the following principles:\n*   **Point Allocation**: Points are awarded strictly based on the completion of specific criteria within the defined time limits.\n*   **Negative Marking**: Deductions apply only for procedural violations, plagiarism, or failure to meet minimum safety standards.\n*   **Tie-Breaking**: In the event of a score tie, priority is given to the participant with the higher difficulty level achieved, followed by the earliest submission time.\n*   **Dispute Resolution**: Any scoring dispute must be filed within 24 hours of result release and reviewed by the Senior Arbitration Panel.\n*   **Weighted Categories**: Specialized categories (e.g., Innovation, Speed, Accuracy) carry distinct multipliers as defined in Section 4.\n\n## 3. Difficulty Levels\nParticipants are assigned to one of three difficulty tiers based on their prior performance history or self-declaration subject to approval. Each tier presents unique constraints and potential point ceilings.\n\n### 3.1 Level 1: Novice\n*   **Constraints**: Standard time limits apply; no complex tool usage permitted.\n*   **Point Ceiling**: Maximum 100 points.\n*   **Criteria**: Focuses on basic execution and adherence to fundamental rules.\n*   **Multiplier**: 1.0x\n\n### 3.2 Level 2: Intermediate\n*   **Constraints**: Extended time limits allowed; basic tool usage permitted.\n*   **Point Ceiling**: Maximum 200 points.\n*   **Criteria**: Requires strategic planning and error management.\n*   **Multiplier**: 1.5x\n\n### 3.3 Level 3: Expert\n*   **Constraints**: Flexible time limits; advanced tool usage required.\n*   **Point Ceiling**: Maximum 500 points.\n*   **Criteria**: Demands innovation, high-level problem solving, and flawless execution.\n*   **Multiplier**: 2.0x\n\n## 4. Category-Specific Multipliers\nTo encourage diverse skill sets, specific performance categories receive automatic multipliers applied to the base score:\n*   **Innovation**: +20% bonus for unique solutions not previously documented.\n*   **Speed**: +10% bonus for completing tasks 15% faster than the average benchmark.\n*   **Accuracy**: +15% bonus for achieving 99%+ precision in data entry or calculation.\n*   **Collaboration**: +10% bonus for teams demonstrating superior peer support metrics.\n\n## 5. Ranking System\nThe final standings are determined by a cumulative score calculated as: `(Base Score \u00d7 Difficulty Multiplier) \u00d7 Category Multipliers`.\n\n### 5.1 Tiered Ranking Structure\n*   **Tier 1 (Challengers)**: Top 10% of participants. Eligible for elite mentorship and advanced resource access.\n*   **Tier 2 (Competitors)**: Next 30% of participants. Eligible for standard rewards and recognition.\n*   **Tier 3 (Participants)**: Remaining 60% of participants. Eligible for participation certificates and feedback.\n\n### 5.2 Dynamic Adjustment\nRankings are recalculated weekly. Participants who move up or down more than two tiers in a single week are flagged for a performance review to ensure the difficulty level matches their current capability.\n\n## 6. Appeals and Review Process\nParticipants dissatisfied with their score may initiate an appeal through the official portal. The appeal must include:\n1.  A specific reference to the rule violated or misinterpreted.\n2.  Supporting evidence (screenshots, logs, or third-party verification).\n3.  A written explanation of the error.\n\nThe Senior Arbitration Panel will review the case within 48 hours. Decisions are final and binding unless a procedural error is proven.\n\n## 7. Effective Date\nThis policy document becomes effective immediately upon digital signing by the Administration Board. Any previous conflicting policies are hereby superseded.\n",
