      "response": "### Comprehensive Scoring Policy Document\n\n**1. General Principles**\n1.1. All scoring is based on objective performance metrics and adherence to defined constraints.\n1.2. Scores are calculated dynamically based on the selected difficulty level.\n1.3. Tie-breaking rules prioritize accuracy, then speed, then consistency.\n\n**2. Difficulty Levels**\n2.1. **Novice**: Reduced time pressure, simplified constraints, and a base multiplier of 1.0x.\n2.2. **Intermediate**: Standard time pressure, moderate constraints, and a base multiplier of 1.5x.\n2.3. **Expert**: High time pressure, complex constraints, and a base multiplier of 2.0x.\n\n**3. Core Scoring Rules**\n3.1. **Accuracy Points**: Awarded 10 points per correct item; deducted 5 points per error.\n3.2. **Speed Bonus**: 1 point added for every 10 seconds under the target time threshold.\n3.3. **Penalty System**: A 20-point deduction applies for any violation of safety or ethical guidelines.\n3.4. **Completion Bonus**: An additional 50 points awarded for finishing all tasks within the allotted time.\n\n**4. Ranking System**\n4.1. **Tier 1 (Elite)**: Total score above 95% of the maximum possible score.\n4.2. **Tier 2 (Advanced)**: Total score between 75% and 95% of the maximum possible score.\n4.3. **Tier 3 (Standard)**: Total score between 50% and 75% of the maximum possible score.\n4.4. **Tier 4 (Beginner)**: Total score below 50% of the maximum possible score.\n\n**5. Appeals and Review**\n5.1. Participants may request a review of their score within 24 hours of submission.\n5.2. Appeals must include specific evidence of calculation errors or rule misinterpretations.\n5.3. Final decisions by the adjudication committee are binding and non-appealable.\n\n***\n\n### Core Scoring Rules Summary\n\n*   **Accuracy**: 10 points per correct item; 5 points deducted per error.\n*   **Speed**: 1 point bonus for every 10 seconds saved against the target time.\n*   **Penalties**: 20-point deduction for any safety or ethical guideline violation.\n*   **Completion**: 50-point bonus for finishing all tasks within the allotted time.\n*   **Difficulty Multipliers**: Novice (1.0x), Intermediate (1.5x), and Expert (2.0x) scales applied to base scores.\n",
