      "u_instruction": "Complete the sentence by listing specific eco-friendly items available for refilling in a single paragraph.",
      "s_gold": "The refillery is stocked with bath and home products. Customers can either bring their own containers or purchase them in-store to fill with the desired items. In order to provide a better understanding of what to expect at the refillery, I can describe the products that are often available, the benefits of refilling, and how to prepare for a visit.\n\nThe refillery typically offers a wide variety of sustainable personal care and household products, such as soaps, shampoos, conditioners, detergent, and cleaning supplies. These products are often packaged in environmentally-friendly solutions, such as glass or metal, and are sourced from local or regional suppliers. Customers may also find unique and specialty products that are not widely available in traditional retail outlets.\n\nOne of the key benefits of refilling is the reduction of waste generated from single-use packaging. By using their own containers or purchasing reusable options from the refillery, customers can feel good about their impact on the environment. Furthermore, many refillable products tend to be more affordable than their single-use counterparts, making shopping sustainably more accessible for everyone.\n\nTo prepare a visit to the refillery, it's important to consider the refill system that is being used. Some refillaries utilize bulk dispensers, where customers can scoop out the desired amount of product right from the container. Others may offer pre-filled, pre-measured containers for convenience, while still others may require customers to pour the product themselves from large containers. Knowing what to expect can help streamline the refilling process and save time.\n\nLastly, the refillery may offer additional services or resources to support sustainable living. This can include advice on reducing household waste, recommendations for similar sustainable products, or demonstrations on ways to further reduce a person's environmental footprint. By engaging with these resources, customers can enhance their overall experience and become informed advocates for sustainable living.\n\nIn summary, visiting a refillery can provide a convenient and cost-effective way to reduce waste and live sustainably. By shopping responsibly, customers can find high-quality personal care and household products that not only benefit them but contribute to a healthier planet.",
